{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionReinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF, Christiano et al. [2017], Ziegler et al.",
    "[2019]) is an important paradigm improving the natural language understanding and generation capabilities of large language models (LLMs).",
    "The core idea of RLHF is to utilize pair-wise comparison between responses from human annotators, as directly collecting absolute reward signals is hard.",
    "There are two stages in RLHF: the reward modeling stage and the policy optimization stage.",
    "The reward modeling stage assumes human preferences follow the Bradley-Terry (BT) model [Bradley and Terry, 1952], allowing a prompt-response pair to be assigned a scalar reward."
  ]
}